<br>
You know how several designers left EQ recently?  I know that if I were told to stop designing for content and to start designing to prolong a cash cow it would make me upset.<br>
<br>
What we see in Luclin is, in my opinion, the result of a directive to keep people playing EQ as long as possible until EQ2 comes out.  You know that increase in fees?  It's not going to affect you, if you promise to lock in the lower rate for a long, long time.  Keep that cash cow rolling!<br>
<br>
Sony, or VI, or whoever is calling this shot is trying to prolong the game by any means necessary.  Sure it's important to factor in time at some point, but they went above and beyond in designing these quests.<br>
<br>
I've spent lots of time in Ssra, working on commanders.  6-10 hours seeing 2-3 commanders and nothing to show for it.  The key happens to be the rare drop on the rare mob.  And I'm not talking just one group either.  I'm talking 18-24 people, constantly pulling 1-4 mobs at a time kind of clearing.  With no payoff.  I was just there last night as a matter of fact.  I love this game, but it is very hard for me to love the end game encounters designed into Luclin.  I don't know, maybe if they put the rare mushroom veil or fetid belt kind of item on the snakes it would provide a bit of upside.  As long as the items don't end up nodrop. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udracomin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dracomin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/1/02 3:08:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1106.topic&index=49>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This is what happens when Uber guilds rule the world....</span><hr size=1> my view on the issue...<br>
<br>
if a majority of uber Luclin mobs had the high AC (near melee resistant), then yes I would have a problem with that.  But Im in favor of a reasonable amount of uber encounters heavily favoring casters and not melee types.<br>
<br>
Reason why?<br>
<br>
Im speaking on my own experience.  But for a long time, in my raiding experience, the emphasis was given to tanks, rogues, and clerics when determining what type of loot to pursue.  I remember when the only caster loot we obtained was the silk that dropped in HoT.  Well, fortunately now the people I raid with seem to take a higher interest in helping casters get good loot.  <br>
<br>
But still a high level guild's highest priorities will be getting a few tanks, rogues, and clerics pimped out.  Sort of makes the rest of the classes, including wizzees feel a bit insignificant.  Add to the fact that clerics get first dibs on mod rods, on getting to group with mana song bard, and are usually only ones to get fed mana from necros.<br>
<br>
Now, when you have a few high AC mobs where melees are averaging 20 to 30 AC mobs, then finally a heavily melee/cleric oriented guild starts to realize they need nukers (a.k.a.  wizards, mages, necros, druids).   Without these high AC mobs, theoretically a hard core raid guild could succeed with a ton of warriors, rogues, clerics plus one chanter, one monk, and one shaman with wizzees and druids as nothing more than port mules.<br>
<br>
So again, having some extremely high AC mobs is good overall, but would be very unfair to melees if it is overdone.<br>
